# S3 Bucket Terraform Export — Walkthrough

## Summary

Exported the S3 bucket `amzn-s3-nova-bucket` from the AWS account into Terraform configuration files, following the same pattern established in the `Terraform-Lambda-Functions` project.

## Data Gathered via AWS CLI

| Configuration | Value |
|---|---|
| **Bucket Name** | `amzn-s3-nova-bucket` |
| **Region** | us-east-1 |
| **Versioning** | Enabled |
| **Encryption** | AES256 (SSE-S3) + BucketKeyEnabled |
| **Public Access Block** | All 4 flags = true (fully blocked) |
| **Bucket Policy** | SES allowed to PutObject |
| **Tags** | Project, Bucket, Environment |
| **Notifications** | 2 Lambda triggers |
| **Lifecycle / CORS / Logging** | Not configured |

### Lambda Notification Triggers
1. `email-attachment-parser` → triggered on `s3:ObjectCreated:*` with prefix `raw-emails/`
2. `Nova-Extractor-Lambda` → triggered on `s3:ObjectCreated:*` with prefix `email-attachment/`

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [main.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Terraform-S3-Bucket/main.tf) | S3 bucket, versioning, encryption, public access block, bucket policy, ownership controls, Lambda notifications |
| [variables.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Terraform-S3-Bucket/variables.tf) | `aws_region` and `aws_account_id` variables |
| [versions.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Terraform-S3-Bucket/versions.tf) | Terraform ≥1.0 + AWS provider ~>5.0 |
| [outputs.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Terraform-S3-Bucket/outputs.tf) | Bucket ID, ARN, region, domain name |
| [s3_config.txt](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Terraform-S3-Bucket/s3_config.txt) | Raw config reference |

## Validation

- ✅ `terraform init` — AWS provider v5.100.0 installed
- ✅ `terraform validate` — Configuration is valid
- ✅ `terraform fmt -check` — Formatting passed
